THIRTY MINUTES TILL DOOM. PLEASE REACT TO CONFIRM ATTENDANCE FOR GROUPING

Reiterating: Once you’ve read this & you’re available to participate, please react with for grouping. Groups will be made randomly unless requested otherwise.
If you’re joining late, no problem! Just ping me in #ooc-chat so I can throw you into a group!

lok, fool of duncetown 🐑 lullaby 12-Jun-21 06:59 PM
@clowns
Thursday, 1 PM
It’s been around twenty minutes since the LQCC received a call from one 'Hana Mori' (verified), a local babysitter and self-proclaimed ‘Craiglist expert’ (unverified). They had requested immediate assistance and ensured, in no small phrasing, that the LQCC would be paid generously for sending the finest detectives. And a lot of them. In the past twenty minutes, you have prepared whatever items you would like to bring and left the office, carpooling (hopefully) to 420 Beech Street to the Erelegan Estate. If any of you are familiar with city banks or investments, you may recognize the prominent familial name. There before you stands a towering house - at least four stories tall - and an immaculate garden. In contrast, a fairly raggedy looking individual stands at 5’4, arms crossed, and blowing a gum bubble. It pops as you draw near.
Hana BOT 12-Jun-21 06:59 PM
“Dang - they really sent over the whole circus, eh?” A raise of their eyebrow. “Whatever. Name’s Hana, don’t tell me y’alls cus I won’t remember. Follow me.” They lead you through some iron gates and around the house to a sprawling backyard. The place is decked out in pinks and yellows - streamers, balloons, huge piles of gifts and finger-food on banquet tables. There’s tell-tale signs that this area is meant for children varying from the child-sized playsets and treehouse to the fact that there’s a cutout of team heart-throb, Juicestin Beaber propped up in the corner. And in the center of this lemonade chaos? There is something garish and atrocious, sticking out even more than Hana themself did. The world’s most defunct looking bounce house. https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/431813460226211850/852301855870156820/unknown.png
3
“Yup. Birthday girl and her friends and … dog went in Barney’s disgusting little slaughterhouse and now they’re gone. Good luck, detectives. Any questions?”

🔒 MISSION ARCHIVES / group-one
lok, fool of duncetown 🐑 lullaby 12-Jun-21 07:22 PM
@roy, mayor of duncetown | kylik @Mimsy ☆ Einstein @turtle | eden @Li💤 ♟ Luciel
THE DANCE FLOOR
You enter. A clown nose appears on your face. The first thing you notice is that balancing is a whole lot harder than you’re used to. On your feet, in place of your shoes, are giant clown shoes + roller blades. And around you…. A roller rink - flashing lights, the scent of pizza, and a giant clown-head-disco-ball hanging from the ceiling. The music on loop is Escape by Rupert Holmes, also known as the Pina Colada Song. Around you are a bunch of animals in 80s clothing, skating around lazily in circles and dancing along to the rhythm. A cafeteria type area is off to the side of the rink, serving hotdogs and nachos and pizza. There are no doors.
Seven Jacobs BOT 12-Jun-21 07:26 PM
"I don't know how to roller blade--" He starts saying as he takes on tentative BIG CLOWN STEP and nearly eats the linoleum. He clutches the closest wall in terror.
3

He's not gonna even try and lift these clown shoes. "..You- uh.........alright?" Maybe they can . form a chain or something. @Mimsy ☆ Einstein

Luciel BOT 12-Jun-21 07:35 PM
A peculier weight on his face... and his feet... then before he knew it, Luciel fell to the ground, hitting his back—thankfully—instead of his head. "..." If he was hurt his expression seldom showed it, although he looked around in bewilderment at the odd smells and sights of what was the beginning of what he understood... was to be a horror film. Glancing to the side, he spotted a few familiar faces... or well, vaguely familiar faces. Human faces. Not one of these odd animal creatures... Can he get up? SWAMP MCSNACKEN
You enter. A clown nose appears on your face. Welcome to the swamp. You are standing on a wooden platform and in front of you is a swamp of neon green Jello. Strung throughout are long ropes made of licorice, wide enough - you think - for you to walk on. In the swap are a veritable ecosystem of gummy creatures ranging from gators to frogs to tiny, tiny fish. In the center of the swamp seems to be a boathouse. MECHANICS
Roll 1d10+dex to make it to the center. 6+ Is you make it You can sabotage each other, putting someone else at a disadvantage (bold & tag the person) You can also help each other, giving someone advantage (bold & tag the person)
